💋A VERY SEXY GRAIN FREE COFFEE CAKE💋
Cake Batter:
2 cups almond flour (substitute with cassava/coconut if you know your ratios or have or nut allergy)💘 
1/3 cup tapioca flour 
1/2 teaspoon baking soda 
1 tablespoon cinnamon
Pinch of salt
2 large eggs or three small 
2/3 cup any sugar of your choice (I ❤️ coconut sugar)
1/3 cup coconut milk or sub another cream
2 Tablespoons avocado oil (or melted cooled coconut oil/butter)
1/2 tablespoon apple cider vinegar 
1/2 teaspoon vanilla
Crumb Topping:
1/3 cup Almond flour
1/2 tablespoon cinnamon 
1/3 cup any sugar of your choice
3 tablespoons cold butter or coconut oil 
Icing:
1/2 cup powdered sugar (I used coconut)
Any milk one tablespoon at a time until your desired texture is found ;)
3 tablespoons tapioca flour
Bake 30-40 min or until a knife comes out clean :)
Cool and top with icing 
I don’t know where this original recipe is from, but this was one of the first grain free desserts I made for myself years ago. I use different ingredients almost every time and it’s always fucking delicious. 
*ive made it without vinegar and it doesn’t come out as fluffy!

CIOPPINO CON MAMA 
1/2 onion thinly sliced
1/2 fennel Bulb thinly sliced
4 garlic cloves thinly sliced 
8 oz clam juice
2 cups white wine
32 oz tomato sauce (ours was cioppino base from Santa Monica Seafood but you can use 4 cups fresh crushed tomatoes add in oregano)
1 pound Shrimp 🍤 
1 pound white fish (halibut)
1 pound clams
1/2 pound baby calamari 
Add in half garlic 5 minutes before you serve !!!
Basil to finish 
💋💋💋
Don’t drop your phone in the soup!

Grain Free Bagels! ☆ 
instant yeast whole packet 
1 tablespoon honey
1/2 cup + 1 tablespoon warm water
1 1/2 cups almond flour
1 1/2 cups tapioca flour 
1/2 cup arrowroot flour (or more tapioca)
1/2 tsp baking powder
1 teaspoon salt
1 egg at room temperature, beaten 
2 tablespoons olive oil or avocado oil 
2 tablespoons apple cider vinegar 
1 tablespoon coconut sugar 

PREPARE•
Boil 4 cups water + 1 tablespoon coconut sugar + big pinch salt
Egg wash•
1 egg + 1 tablespoon milk (I use almond)
Line a baking tray with parchment paper and oil 
Preheat oven to 375 Fahrenheit.

DOUGH• Mix yeast with warm water and honey and let sit aside for 5-7 minutes until bloomed
Big bowl mix flours, coconut sugar, baking powder, salt. 
Create a well in the center and add yeast mixture, egg, and olive oil and vinegar
Mix should be shaggy ;)
Cover with damp towel and let rise for 30 min
With oiled hands mold into 6 bagel sized 🛸 and place on a lined baking tray. 
Cover and let rise again 
Poke holes with an oiled finger. 

BATH• water pop one in at a time one minute on each side(if they stick to the bottom right away give them a little help) 
Take them out using a slotted spoon to drain the water and place back on your baking tray. 

BAKE• Big slob of egg milk mixture and top with seasoning pop in the oven 30 minutes until golden brown. Let them cool completely before eating 🥯 💋
